Sentencas: Research and development of Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) technology has been carried out at the Julich research center for more than 20 years.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: A standard cell design based on a porous nickel cermet has been established and tested with stationary conditions, for which a power density of more than 1.50 W/cm(2) at 800 degrees C in H-2 was obtained.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: In order to broaden the field of possible applications, new cell designs have been developed.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: Among those are metal-supported SOFCs (MSC), which promise increased robustness against thermal-, mechanical and chemical stresses, as well as cheaper production costs.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: While the MSC development may find an application in mobile devices another cell design concept aims at much lower operating temperatures.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: For this cell type a very thin zirconia membrane is deposited on top of a standard anode support via a multi-step sol/gel-route.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs

Sentencas: With this setup a reduction of the operating temperature to 600 degrees C with a power output of 1.25 W/cm(2) could be demonstrated.
Titulo: Advances beyond traditional SOFC cell designs
